<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="292" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,800,1943]" pageId="3" pageNumber="292">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,1772,1799]" pageId="3" pageNumber="292">Discussion.</emphasis>
The new species slightly resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Jin, 1995" authorityName="Jin" authorityYear="1995" box="[755,1092,1772,1799]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Alloteratura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="292" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="plauta">
<emphasis box="[755,975,1773,1799]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="292">Alloteratura plauta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Jin, X. B." box="[984,1092,1772,1799]" pageId="3" pageNumber="292" pagination="193 - 205" refId="ref3497" refString="Jin, X. B. (1995) Remarks on the genus Alloteratura Hebard and new species from Indo-Malayan regions. (Orthoptera: Tettigonioidea: Meconematidae). Entomologia Sinica, 2 (3), 193 - 205. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1744 - 7917.1995. tb 00040. x" type="journal article" year="1995">Jin, 1995</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs from the latter in: male cerci upcurved in the middle, inner margin with a lamellate lobe expanded; epiphallus thick, horsehead-shaped in lateral view.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="292" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,800,1943]" pageId="3" pageNumber="292">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1881,1907]" pageId="3" pageNumber="292">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name of new species is derived from apical morphology of epiphallus, Latin 
<emphasis box="[1275,1356,1881,1907]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="292">flagell-</emphasis>
means fan-shaped.
</paragraph>
